The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, February 08, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE FILM FEST				 																																	(Gorky Sadan, Feb 10-14)				 																																	lOrganised jointly by Eisentein Cine Club and Ritwik Memorial Trust, the festival marks the 50th anniversary of the masters maiden film, Nagarik. A special attraction for Ritwik fans will be the screening of three of his unfinished films				 																THE EXHIBITION				 																																	(Indian Museum, Feb. 8-16)				 																																	lThe exhibition will be held alongside a three-day seminar on Approaches to Indian Art (February 8-10). Organised by Indian Museum on its 189th anniversary, the seminar-cum-exhibition is being organised to mark the birth centenary of Niharranjan Ray				 																THE BOOK				 																																	(Githa Hariharan)				 																																	lSet in New Delhi of 2000, this sharp and gripping narrative traces some ordinary lives besieged, of men and women struggling to cope with hatred as fundamentalism lands on the doorstep of the protagonist, a history teacher				 																THE CD				 																																	(Simon amp; Garfunkel)				 																																	lThis three-CD set chronicles the entire career of arguably the greatest pop duo of our time. Featured are all their hit songs, as well as 15 previously unreleased gems, including demos, live performances and unissued studio recordings
